ching external docs.\\n\\n## Files to Modify\\n\\n1. **`.claude/skills/agent-integration/researcher.md`** — Refocus on external-only discovery, remove internal Entire doc reading, output a one-pager\\n2. **`.claude/skills/agent-integration/test-writer.md`** — Reference the one-pager for agent-specific info\\n3. **`.claude/skills/agent-integration/implementer.md`** — Reference the one-pager for agent-specific info, keep internal doc reading\\n4. **`.claude/skills/agent-integration/SKILL.md`** — Update phase descriptions to reflect the one-pager handoff\\n\\n## Changes\\n\\n### 1. `researcher.md` — External-Only, Produces One-Pager\\n\\n**Remove:** Phase 1 (Architecture Inspection) reads too many internal files (`agent.go`, `event.go`, `hook_registry.go`, `lifecycle.go`, checklist, reference implementations). Most of that is the implementer's job.\\n\\n**Keep from Phase 1:** Read `docs/architecture/agent-guide.md` — the researcher needs this to understand what Entire expects from agents (EventType names, required interfaces, hook patterns) so it can create accurate mappings in the one-pager.\\n\\n**Keep:** Phase 2 (Static Capability Checks) — binary probing, help scanning, config dir discovery, web search for docs.\\n\\n**Keep:** Phase 3 (Test Script Creation) — the probe script for capturing real hook payloads.\\n\\n**Keep:** Phase 4 (Execution & Analysis) — running the script, analyzing captures.\\n\\n**Replace Phase 5 (Compatibility Report)** with a new output: an **implementation one-pager** written to `cmd/entire/cli/agent/$AGENT_SLUG/AGENT.md`.\\n\\n**One-pager template:**\\n\\n```markdown\\n# $AGENT_NAME — Integration One-Pager\\n\\n## Verdict: COMPATIBLE / PARTIAL / INCOMPATIBLE\\n\\n## Binary\\n- Name: `$AGENT_BIN`\\n- Version: ...\\n- Install: ... (how to install if not present)\\n\\n## Hook Mechanism\\n- Config file: `~/.config/$AGENT_SLUG/settings.json` (exact path)\\n- Config format: JSON / YAML / TOML\\n- Hook registration: ... (how hooks are declared — 