_id\":\"toolu_01JtwpfgTHALsB2xikRDwTqw\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"     1→# Plan: Refocus Research Phase, Add Implementation One-Pager\\n     2→\\n     3→## Context\\n     4→\\n     5→The 3-phase agent integration pipeline (research → write-tests → implement) has overlap: research reads the same internal Entire docs that the implementer re-reads, and both phases may search external agent docs independently. The fix: **research focuses purely on external discovery** and produces a structured \\\"implementation one-pager\\\" that both test-writer and implementer reference instead of re-searching external docs.\\n     6→\\n     7→## Files to Modify\\n     8→\\n     9→1. **`.claude/skills/agent-integration/researcher.md`** — Refocus on external-only discovery, remove internal Entire doc reading, output a one-pager\\n    10→2. **`.claude/skills/agent-integration/test-writer.md`** — Reference the one-pager for agent-specific info\\n    11→3. **`.claude/skills/agent-integration/implementer.md`** — Reference the one-pager for agent-specific info, keep internal doc reading\\n    12→4. **`.claude/skills/agent-integration/SKILL.md`** — Update phase descriptions to reflect the one-pager handoff\\n    13→\\n    14→## Changes\\n    15→\\n    16→### 1. `researcher.md` — External-Only, Produces One-Pager\\n    17→\\n    18→**Remove:** Phase 1 (Architecture Inspection) reads too many internal files (`agent.go`, `event.go`, `hook_registry.go`, `lifecycle.go`, checklist, reference implementations). Most of that is the implementer's job.\\n    19→\\n    20→**Keep from Phase 1:** Read `docs/architecture/agent-guide.md` — the researcher needs this to understand what Entire expects from agents (EventType names, required interfaces, hook patterns) so it can create accurate mappings in the one-pager.\\n    21→\\n    22→**Keep:** Phase 2 (Static Capability Checks) — binary probing, help scanning, config dir discovery, web search for docs.\\n    23→\\n    24→**Keep:** Phase 3 (Te