ress\",\"data\":{\"message\":{\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_015meEDyqxhZfRwrMG59Hv7q\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"     1→---\\n     2→name: agent-integration\\n     3→description: >\\n     4→  Run all three agent integration phases sequentially: research, write-tests,\\n     5→  and implement. For individual phases, use /agent-integration:research,\\n     6→  /agent-integration:write-tests, or /agent-integration:implement.\\n     7→  Use when the user says \\\"integrate agent\\\", \\\"add agent support\\\", or wants\\n     8→  to run the full agent integration pipeline end-to-end.\\n     9→---\\n    10→\\n    11→# Agent Integration — Full Pipeline\\n    12→\\n    13→Run all three phases of agent integration in a single session. Parameters are collected once and reused across all phases.\\n    14→\\n    15→## Parameters\\n    16→\\n    17→Collect these before starting (ask the user if not provided):\\n    18→\\n    19→| Parameter | Example | Description |\\n    20→|-----------|---------|-------------|\\n    21→| `AGENT_NAME` | \\\"Windsurf\\\" | Human-readable agent name |\\n    22→| `AGENT_SLUG` | \\\"windsurf\\\" | Lowercase slug for file/directory paths |\\n    23→| `AGENT_BIN` | \\\"windsurf\\\" | CLI binary name |\\n    24→| `LIVE_COMMAND` | \\\"windsurf --project .\\\" | Full command to launch agent |\\n    25→| `EVENTS_OR_UNKNOWN` | \\\"unknown\\\" | Known hook event names, or \\\"unknown\\\" |\\n    26→\\n    27→## Architecture References\\n    28→\\n    29→These documents define the agent integration contract:\\n    30→\\n    31→- **Implementation guide**: `docs/architecture/agent-guide.md` — Step-by-step code templates, event mapping, testing patterns\\n    32→- **Integration checklist**: `docs/architecture/agent-integration-checklist.md` — Design principles and validation criteria\\n    33→\\n    34→## Pipeline\\n    35→\\n    36→Run these three phases in order. Each phase builds on the previous phase's output.\\n    37→\\n    38→### Phase 1: Research\\n    39→\\n    40→Discover the agent's hook mechanism, transcript format, and configuration through binary probing and documentation research. Produces an implementation one-pager at `cmd/entire/cli/agent/$AGENT_SLUG/AGENT.md` that the other phases use as their single source of agent-specific information.\\n    41→\\n    42→Read and follow the research procedure from `.claude/skills/agent-integration/researcher.md`.\\n    43→\\n    44→**Expected output:** Implementation one-pager at `cmd/entire/cli/agent/$AGENT_SLUG/AGENT.md` and a test script at `scripts/test-$AGENT_SLUG-agent-integration.sh`.\\n    45→\\n    46→**Gate:** If the verdict is INCOMPATIBLE, stop and discuss with the user before proceeding.\\n    47→\\n    48→### Phase 2: Write Tests\\n    49→\\n    50→Generate the E2E test suite using the one-pager for agent-specific information (binary name, CLI flags, interactive mode support).\\n    51→\\n    52→Read and follow the write-tests procedure from `.claude/skills/agent-integration/test-writer.md`.\\n    53→\\n    54→**Expected output:** E2E agent runner at `e2e/agents/$AGENT_SLUG.go` and any agent-specific test scenarios.\\n    55→\\n    56→### Phase 3: Implement\\n    57→\\n    58→Build the Go agent package using E2E-driven development. Reads internal Entire docs (agent-guide, checklist, interfaces) and uses the one-pager for all agent-specific details (hook format, transcript location, config structure).\\n    59→\\n    60→Read and follow the implement procedure from `.claude/skills/agent-integration/implementer.md`.\\n    61→\\n    62→**Expected output:** Complete agent package at `cmd/entire/cli/agent/$AGENT_SLUG/` with all tests passing.\\n    63→\\n    64→## Final Validation\\n    65→\\n    66→After all three phases, run the complete validation:\\n    67→\\n    68→```bash\\n    69→mise run fmt      # Format\\n    70→mise run lint     # Lint\\n    71→mise run test:ci  # All tests (unit