Doc\\n    34→\\n    35→Read `docs/architecture/checkpoint-scenarios.md` for the state machine and scenarios the tests should cover.\\n    36→\\n    37→### Step 4: Create Agent Implementation\\n    38→\\n    39→Read `cmd/entire/cli/agent/$AGENT_SLUG/AGENT.md` (the one-pager from the research phase) for all agent-specific information:\\n    40→- Binary name → \\\"Binary\\\" section\\n    41→- Prompt flags → \\\"CLI Flags\\\" section\\n    42→- Interactive mode → \\\"CLI Flags\\\" section\\n    43→- Transient error patterns → \\\"Gaps & Limitations\\\" section (use defaults if not listed)\\n    44→- Bootstrap setup → \\\"Config Preservation\\\" section\\n    45→\\n    46→**If something is missing from the one-pager**, you may search external docs — but update `AGENT.md` with anything new you discover.\\n    47→\\n    48→Add a new `Agent` implementation in `e2e/agents/${agent_slug}.go`:\\n    49→\\n    50→**Pattern to follow** (based on existing implementations like `claude.go`, `gemini.go`, `opencode.go`):\\n    51→\\n    52→```go\\n    53→package agents\\n    54→\\n    55→import (\\n    56→\\t\\\"context\\\"\\n    57→\\t\\\"errors\\\"\\n    58→\\t\\\"fmt\\\"\\n    59→\\t\\\"os\\\"\\n    60→\\t\\\"os/exec\\\"\\n    61→\\t\\\"strings\\\"\\n    62→\\t\\\"syscall\\\"\\n    63→\\t\\\"time\\\"\\n    64→)\\n    65→\\n    66→func init() {\\n    67→\\tif env := os.Getenv(\\\"E2E_AGENT\\\"); env != \\\"\\\" && env != \\\"${agent-slug}\\\" {\\n    68→\\t\\treturn\\n    69→\\t}\\n    70→\\tRegister(&${AgentName}{})\\n    71→\\t// Optional: limit concurrency for rate-limited agents\\n    72→\\t// RegisterGate(\\\"${agent-slug}\\\", 1)\\n    73→}\\n    74→\\n    75→type ${AgentName} struct{}\\n    76→\\n    77→func (a *${AgentName}) Name() string               { return \\\"${agent-slug}\\\" }\\n    78→func (a *${AgentName}) Binary() string             { return \\\"${binary-name}\\\" }\\n    79→func (a *${AgentName}) EntireAgent() string        { return \\\"${entire-agent-name}\\\" }\\n    80→func (a *${AgentName}) PromptPattern() string      { return `${prompt-regex}` }\\n    81→func (a *${AgentName}) TimeoutMultiplier() float64 { return 1.0 }\\n    82→\\n    83→func (a *${AgentName}) Bootstrap() error {\\n    84→\\t// CI-specific setup: auth config, API key injection, warmup, etc.\\n    85→\\t// Must be idempotent. Called once before any tests run.\\n    86→\\treturn nil\\n    87→}\\n    88→\\n    89→func (a *${AgentName}) IsTransientError(out Output, err error) bool {\\n    90→\\tif err == nil {\\n    91→\\t\\treturn false\\n    92→\\t}\\n    93→\\tcombined := out.Stdout + out.Stderr\\n    94→\\tfor _, p := range []string{\\\"overloaded\\\", \\\"rate limit\\\", \\\"503\\\", \\\"529\\\"} {\\n    95→\\t\\tif strings.Contains(combined, p) {\\n    96→\\t\\t\\treturn true\\n    97→\\t\\t}\\n    98→\\t}\\n    99→\\treturn false\\n   100→}\\n   101→\\n   102→func (a *${AgentName}) RunPrompt(ctx context.Context, dir string, prompt string, opts ...Option) (Output, error) {\\n   103→\\tcfg := &runConfig{}\\n   104→\\tfor _, o := range opts {\\n   105→\\t\\to(cfg)\\n   106→\\t}\\n   107→\\n   108→\\targs := []string{/* agent CLI flags for non-interactive prompt execution */}\\n   109→\\tcmd := exec.CommandContext(ctx, a.Binary(), args...)\\n   110→\\tcmd.Dir = dir\\n   111→\\tcmd.Env = append(os.Environ(), \\\"ENTIRE_TEST_TTY=0\\\")\\n   112→\\tcmd.SysProcAttr = &syscall.SysProcAttr{Setpgid: true}\\n   113→\\tcmd.Cancel = func() error {\\n   114→\\t\\treturn syscall.Kill(-cmd.Process.Pid, syscall.SIGKILL)\\n   115→\\t}\\n   116→\\n   117→\\tvar stdout, stderr strings.Builder\\n   118→\\tcmd.Stdout = &stdout\\n   119→\\tcmd.Stderr = &stderr\\n   120→\\n   121→\\terr := cmd.Run()\\n   122→\\texitCode := 0\\n   123→\\tif err != nil {\\n   124→\\t\\texitErr := &exec.ExitError{}\\n   125→\\t\\tif errors.As(err, &exitErr) {\\n   126→\\t\\t\\texitCode = exitErr.ExitCode()\\n   127→\\t\\t} else {\\n   128→\\t\\t\\texitCode = -1\\n   129→\\t\\t}\\n   130→\\t}\\n   131→\\n   132→\\treturn Output{\\n   133→\\t\\tCommand:  a.Binary() + \\\" \\\" + strings.Join(args, \\\" \\\"),\\n   134→\\t\\tStdout:   stdout.String(),\\n   135→\\t\\tStderr:   stderr.String(),\\n   136→\\t\\tExitCode: exitCode,\\n   137→\\t}, err\\n   138→}\\n   139→\\n   140→func (a *${AgentName}) StartSession(ctx context.Context, dir string) (Session, error) {\\n   141→\\t// Use NewTmuxSession for interactive PTY support.\\n   142→\\t// Return nil if agent doesn't support interactive mode.\\n   143→\\tname := fmt.Sprintf(\\\"${agent-slug}-test-%d\\\", time.Now().UnixNano())\\n   144→\\ts, err := NewTmuxSession(name, dir, nil, a.Binary(), /* interactive args */)\\n   145→\\tif err != nil {\\n   146→\\t\\treturn nil, err\\n   147→\\t}\\n   148→\\treturn s, nil\\n   149→}\\n   150→```\\n   151→\\n   152→Key implementation details:\\n   153→- Self-register in `init()` with `Register()`, gated by `E2E_AGENT` env var\\n   154→- Use `RegisterGate(\\\"name\\\", N)` if the agent's API has strict rate limits (e.g., Gemini uses gate of 1)\\n   155→- `Bootstrap()` handles CI-specific one-time setup (auth config, API key injection)\\n   156→- `IsTransientError()` identifies retryable API failures — `RepoState.RunPrompt` retries once on transient errors\\n   157→- `RunPrompt()` uses `exec.CommandContext` with `Setpgid: true` and process-group kill for clean cancellation\\n   158→- `StartSession()` uses `NewTmuxSession` for interactive PTY tests; return `nil` if interactive mode isn't supported\\n   159→- Use `AGENT.md` (the one-pager) for CLI flags, prompt passing mechanism, and env vars\\n   160→\\n   161→### Step 5: Update SetupRepo (if needed)\\n   162→\\n   163→Check if `testutil.SetupRepo` in `e2e/testutil/repo.go` needs agent-specific configuration. Look for the existing `if agent.Name() == \\\"opencode\\\"` block as an example:\\n   164→\\n   165→- Agent-specific config files that must exist before `entire enable`\\n   166→- Permission or auth config files\\n   167→- Environment variables needed for hook testing\\n   168→\\n   169→If no special setup is needed, skip this step.\\n   170→\\n   171→### Step 6: Write E2E Test Scenarios\\n   172→\\n   173→Existing tests are agent-agnostic (they use `ForEachAgent`), so they should already work with the new agent. **Only create new test files if the agent has unique behaviors** that existing scenarios don't cover.\\n   174→\\n   175→Check if all existing scenarios work by reviewing:\\n   176→- Does the agent support non-interactive prompt mode? (required for `RunPrompt`)\\n   177→- Does the agent create files when prompted? (required for basic workflow)\\n   178→- Does the agent support git operations? (required for commit scenarios)\\n   179→- Does the agent support interactive mode? (required for interactive tests — can return nil from `StartSession`)\\n   180→\\n   181→If the agent has unique behaviors, create new test files in `e2e/tests/`:\\n   182→\\n   183→```go\\n   184→//go:build e2e\\n   185→\\n   186→package tests\\n   187→\\n   188→import (\\n   189→\\t\\\"context\\\"\\n   190→\\t\\\"testing\\\"\\n   191→\\t\\\"time\\\"\\n   192→\\n   193→\\t\\\"github.com/entireio/cli/e2e/testutil\\\"\\n   194→)\\n   195→\\n   196→func TestAgentSpecificBehavior(t *testing.T) {\\n   197→\\ttestutil.ForEachAgent(t, 2*time.Minute, func(t *testing.T, s *testutil.RepoState, ctx context.Context) {\\n   198→\\t\\t// Skip for agents that don't apply\\n   199→\\t\\tif s.Agent.Name() != \\\"${agent-slug}\\\" {\\n   200→\\t\\t\\tt.Skip(\\\"only applies to ${agent-slug}\\\")\\n   201→\\t\\t}\\n   202→\\n   203→\\t\\t// Use s.RunPrompt for non-interactive, s.StartSession for interactive\\n   204→\\t\\t_, err := s.RunPrompt(t, ctx,\\n   205→\\t\\t\\t\\\"create a file at hello.txt with 'hello world'. Do not ask for confirmation.\\\")\\n   206→\\t\\tif err != nil {\\n   207→\\t\\t\\tt.Fatalf(\\\"agent failed: %v\\\", err)\\n   208→\\t\\t}\\n   209→\\n   210→\\t\\ttestutil.AssertFileExists(t, s.Dir, \\\"hello.txt\\\")\\n   211→\\t})\\n   212→}\\n   213→```\\n   214→\\n   215→See `e2e/README.md` for the canonical reference on structure, debugging, and CI workflows.\\n   216→\\n   217→### Step 7: Verify\\n   218→\\n   219→After writing the code:\\n   220→\\n   221→1. **Lint check**: `mise run lint` — ensure no lint errors\\n   222→2. **Compile check**: `go test -c -tags=e2e ./e2e/tests` — compile-only with the build tag to verify the code compiles\\n   223→3. **List what to run**: Print the exact E2E commands but do NOT run them (they cost money):\\n   224→   ```bash\\n   225→   mise run test:e2e:${agent_slug} TestSingleSessionManualCommit\\n   226→   ```\\n   227→4. **Debug failures**: If tests fail, use `/debug-e2e {artifact-dir}` to diagnose — artifacts are auto-captured to `e2e/artifacts/{timestamp}/`\\n   228→5. **Add mise task**: Remind the user to add a `test:e2e:${agent_slug}` task in `mise.toml` and update CI workflows\\n   229→\\n   230→## Key Conventions\\n   231→\\n   232→- **Build tag**: All E2E test files must have `//go:build e2e` as the first line\\n   233→- **Package**: `package tests` for test files in `e2e/tests/`; `package agents` for agent implementations in `e2e/agents/`\\n   234→- **Parallel**: `ForEachAgent` handles parallelism — do not call `t.Parallel()` inside the callback\\n   235→- **Repo setup**: `ForEachAgent` calls `SetupRepo` automatically — do not call it manually\\n   236→- **Prompts**: Write prompts inline in the test. Include \\\"Do not ask for confirmation\\\" to prevent agent stalling\\n   237→- **Assertions**: Use helpers from `e2e/testutil/assertions.go` — see `AssertFileExists`, `WaitForCheckpoint`, `AssertCommitLinkedToCheckpoint`, `ValidateCheckpointDeep`, etc.\\n   238→- **CLI operations**: Use the `e2e/entire` package (`entire.Enable`, `entire.RewindList`, `entire.Rewind`, etc.) — never call the binary via raw `exec.Command`\\n   239→- **No hardcoded paths**: Use `s.Dir` for repo paths, `s.ArtifactDir` for artifacts\\n   240→- **Console logging**: All operations through `s.RunPrompt`, `s.Git`, `s.Send`, `s.WaitFor` are automatically logged to `console.log`\\n   241→- **Transient errors**: `s.RunPrompt` auto-retries once on transient API errors via `IsTransientError`\\n   242→- **Interactive tests**: Use `s.StartSession`, `s.Send`, `s.WaitFor` — tmux pane is auto-captured in artifacts\\n   243→- **Run commands**: `mise run test:e2e:${slug} TestName` — see `e2e/README.md` for all options\\n   244→- **Do NOT run E2E tests**: They make real API calls. Only write the code and print commands.\\n   245→- **Debugging failures**: If the user runs tests and they fail, use `/debug-e2e` with the artifact directory to diagnose CLI-level issues (hooks, checkpoints, session phases, attribution)\\n   246→\\n   247→## Output\\n   248→\\n   249→Summarize what was created/modified:\\n   250→- Files added or modified\\n   251→- New agent implementation details (how it invokes the agent, auth setup, concurrency gate)\\n   252→- Any agent-specific test scenarios added\\n   253→- Commands to run the tests (for user to execute manually)\\n   254→- If tests fail, suggest using `/debug-e2e {artifact-dir}` for root cause analysis\\n   255→- Reminder to update `mise.toml` and CI workflows\\n   256→\"}]},\"uuid\":\"0f82482c-dfc1-4b0e-8eef-24edae236ab0\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-27T01:09:55.398Z\"},\"normalizedMessages\":[],\"type\":\"agent_progress\",\"prompt\":\"I need to audit the agent integration skill files in `.claude/skills/agent-integration/`. Help me understand the broader context by finding:\\n\\n1. **Existing agent implementations**: Run `Glob(\\\"cmd/entire/cli/agent/*/\\\")` to see all agent packages. Then for one agent (e.g., claude-code or gemini), read the file listing to understand the actual file structure (do they already have AGENT.md files? what files exist?).\\n\\n2. **The agent-guide.md**: Read `docs/architecture/agent-guide.md` — I need to understand what EventType names and interface