.go`, checklist, reference implementations). Most of that is the implementer's job.\\n\\n**Keep from Phase 1:** Read `docs/architecture/agent-guide.md` — the researcher needs this to understand what Entire expects from agents (EventType names, required interfaces, hook patterns) so it can create accurate mappings in the one-pager.\\n\\n**Keep:** Phase 2 (Static Capability Checks) — binary probing, help scanning, config dir discovery, web search for docs.\\n\\n**Keep:** Phase 3 (Test Script Creation) — the probe script for capturing real hook payloads.\\n\\n**Keep:** Phase 4 (Execution & Analysis) — running the script, analyzing captures.\\n\\n**Replace Phase 5 (Compatibility Report)** with a new output: an **implementation one-pager** written to `cmd/entire/cli/agent/$AGENT_SLUG/AGENT.md`.\\n\\n**One-pager template:**\\n\\n```markdown\\n# $AGENT_NAME — Integration One-Pager\\n\\n## Verdict: COMPATIBLE / PARTIAL / INCOMPATIBLE\\n\\n## Binary\\n- Name: `$AGENT_BIN`\\n- Version: ...\\n- Install: ... (how to install if not present)\\n\\n## Hook Mechanism\\n- Config file: `~/.config/$AGENT_SLUG/settings.json` (exact path)\\n- Config format: JSON / YAML / TOML\\n- Hook registration: ... (how hooks are declared — JSON objects, env vars, etc.)\\n- Hook names and when they fire:\\n  | Native Hook Name | When It Fires | Entire EventType |\\n  |-----------------|---------------|-----------------|\\n  | `on_session_start` | Agent session begins | `SessionStart` |\\n  | ... | ... | ... |\\n- Hook input (stdin JSON): ... (exact fields with example payload)\\n\\n## Transcript\\n- Location: `~/.config/$AGENT_SLUG/sessions/<id>/transcript.jsonl`\\n- Format: JSONL / JSON array / other\\n- Session ID extraction: ... (from hook payload field or directory name)\\n- Example entry: `{\\\"role\\\": \\\"user\\\", \\\"content\\\": \\\"...\\\"}`\\n\\n## Config Preservation\\n- Keys to preserve when modifying: ... (or \\\"use read-modify-write on entire file\\\")\\n- Settings that affect hook behavior: ...\\n\\n## CLI Flags\\n- Non-interactive prompt: `$AGENT_BIN --prompt \\\"...\\\" --no-confirm`\\n- Interactive mode: `$AGENT_BIN` (or \\\"not supported\\\")\\n- Relevant env vars: ...\\n\\n## Gaps & Limitations\\n- ... (anything that doesn't map cleanly)\\n\\n## Captured Payloads\\n- See `.entire/tmp/probe-$AGENT_SLUG-*/captures/` for raw JSON captures\\n```\\n\\n**Key change:** The one-pager includes the **Entire EventType mapping** (which native hook → which EventType). Research can do this mapping because it's a simple table based on the hook names — it doesn't need to read Entire source code to know that \\\"session start\\\" maps to `SessionStart`. The implementer then uses this table directly when writing `lifecycle.go`.\\n\\n### 2. `test-writer.md` — Reference One-Pager\\n\\n**Update prerequisites:**\\n```\\n- The research command's one-pager at `cmd/entire/cli/agent/$AGENT_SLUG/AGENT.md`\\n- If no one-pager exists, ask the user for: binary name, prompt CLI flags, interactive mode support\\n```\\n\\n**Update Step 4 (Create Agent Implementation):**\\n- Binary name → from one-pager \\\"Binary\\\" section\\n- Prompt flags → from one-pager \\\"CLI Flags\\\" section\\n- Interactive mode → from one-pager \\\"CLI Flags\\\" section\\n- Transient error patterns → from one-pager \\\"Gaps & Limitations\\\" or use defaults\\n- Bootstrap setup → from one-pager \\\"Config Preservation\\\" section\\n\\n**Add instruction:** \\\"Check the one-pager first for all agent-specific information. If something is missing, you may search external docs — but update `AGENT.md` with anything new you discover.\\\"\\n\\n### 3. `implementer.md` — Reference One-Pager, Keep Internal Docs\\n\\n**Step 1 (Read Implementation Guide):** Unchanged — reads internal Entire docs (`agent-guide.md`, checklist, `agent.go`, `event.go`). This is the only place these get read.\\n\\n**Step 2 (Read Reference Implementation):** Update to say: \\\"Check the one-pager's 'Gaps & Limitations' section to pick the best reference — choose an agent with a similar hook mechanism.\\\"\\n\\n**Step 3 (Create Stubs):** Update each sub-item to reference the one-pager:\\n- `types.go` JSON tags → from one-pager \\\"Hook input (stdin JSON)\\\"\\n- `hooks.go` config file path → from one-pager \\\"Config file\\\" and \\\"Hook registration\\\"\\n- `lifecycle.go` event mapping → from one-pager \\\"Hook names\\\" table\\n- `transcript.go` format → from one-pager \\\"Transcript\\\" section\\n\\n**Steps 4-12 (E2E Tiers):** Add a standing instruction: \\\"If you need agent-specific information (hook format, transcript location, config structure), check `AGENT.md` first. If AGENT.md doesn't cover what you need, you may search external docs — but always update AGENT.md with anything new you discover so future steps don't need to re-search.\\\"\\n\\n### 4. `SKILL.md` — Update Phase Descriptions\\n\\n**Phase 1 (Research):** Update description to emphasize external-only focus and one-pager output:\\n```\\nDiscover the agent's hook mechanism, transcript format, and configuration\\nthrough binary probing and documentation research. Produces an implementation\\none-pager at `cmd/entire/cli/agent/$AGENT_SLUG/AGENT.md` that the other\\nphases use as their single source of agent-specific information.\\n```\\n\\n**Phase 2 (Write Tests):** Update expected output to mention it uses the one-pager.\\n\\n**Phase 3 (Implement):** Already updated from previous commit. No further changes.\\n\\n**Gate:** Keep the INCOMPATIBLE gate after Phase 1.\\n\\n## What This Achieves\\n\\n| Before | After |\\n|--------|-------|\\n| Research reads all internal Entire docs | Research reads only `agent-guide.md`; implementer reads the rest |\\n| Implementer re-reads internal docs | Same (but no duplication) |\\n| Both phases may search external docs | Research does primary external search; other phases check one-pager first, fall back to external search, and update one-pager |\\n| Research produces a report (consumed once) | Research produces a one-pager (consumed by both later phases) |\\n| Test-writer asks user if no research | Test-writer reads one-pager directly |\\n| Implementer has no record of external findings | One-pager persists as `AGENT.md` in the package |\\n\\n## AGENT.md Lifecycle\\n\\n- **Created** by research phase\\n- **Read** by test-writer and implementer phases (their primary source of agent-specific info)\\n- **Updated** during implementation if E2E failures reveal new information\\n- **Committed** to the repo — serves as development documentation for future maintainers\\n\\n## Verification\\n\\n1. Read updated `researcher.md` — confirm no internal Entire doc reading, confirm one-pager output\\n2. Read updated `test-writer.md` — confirm it references one-pager, confirm no external doc searching\\n3. Read updated `implementer.md` — confirm it references one-pager for agent-specific info, confirm no external doc searching\\n4. Read updated `SKILL.md` — confirm phase descriptions reflect the handoff\\n5. Mentally trace through a hypothetical agent integration to verify no phase needs to re-search external docs\\n\"},\"sourceToolAssistantUUID\":\"c063cd65-e504-4991-be92-0ab1728db708\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"bf78b0b8-16d1-4c84-986e-67f1ab5678bc\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/wt/kiro-oneshot\",\"sessionId\":\"46c073e8-9109-4faf-bd0b-fe9c0209ac96\",\"version\":\"2.1.61\",\"gitBranch\":\"alisha/kiro-oneshot\",\"slug\":\"snuggly-beaming-peacock\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01EDqXBPxmRt64yAvA1CfeVk\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_013kUu6S5zrKhzqmytKhLG56\",\"name\":\"ExitPlanMode\",\"input\":{\"allowedPrompts\":[{\"tool\":\"Bash\",\"prompt\":\"grep across skill files to verify fixes\"}],\"plan\":\"# Audit: Agent Integration Skills (Post One-Pager Refactor)\\n\\n## Context\\n\\nThe one-pager refactor was just implemented. This a