122`\\n**Problem:** Phase 2 runs 7 static checks (binary, help, version, hook keywords, session keywords, config dir, docs). These results aren't captured in the one-pager template. The verdict (COMPATIBLE/PARTIAL/INCOMPATIBLE) depends on these checks, but there's no place to record the detailed results.\\n**Fix:** Add a `## Static Checks` section to the template between `## Verdict` and `## Binary`:\\n```markdown\\n## Static Checks\\n| Check | Result | Notes |\\n|-------|--------|-------|\\n| Binary present | PASS/FAIL | path |\\n| Help available | PASS/FAIL | |\\n| ... | ... | ... |\\n```\\n\\n### 4. `implementer.md` Step 13 partially redundant with Step 3\\n\\n**File:** `implementer.md:227-231`\\n**Problem:** Step 13 says \\\"Register hook commands: Search `cmd/entire/cli/` for where hook subcommands are registered and add the new agent\\\" — but Step 3 already says to wire up blank imports in `hooks_cmd.go`. Step 13 also says \\\"Verify registration: The `init()` function...\\\" which Step 3 also covers.\\n**Fix:** Simplify Step 13 to just verification: \\\"Verify registration by running `mise run test:ci`. The `init()` in `${AGENT_SLUG}.go` and blank import in `hooks_cmd.go` (from Step 3) should be sufficient.\\\"\\n\\n### 5. `test-writer.md` Step 1 reads 8 files — no priority guidance\\n\\n**File:** `test-writer.md:12-23`\\n**Problem:** Step 1 lists 8 infrastructure files to read. This is a lot of context to load. The most critical files for writing a new agent runner are `agent.go` (interface) and one existing agent (e.g., `claude.go`), not all 8.\\n**Fix:** Add a note: \\\"**Most critical:** Focus on items 3 (`agent.go` — the interface you must implement) and read one existing agent implementation (e.g., `e2e/agents/claude.go`) as a reference. Skim the rest for context.\\\"\\n\\n### 6. One-pager template doesn't list valid EventType values\\n\\n**File:** `researcher.md:95-99`\\n**Problem:** The hook mapping table has an \\\"Entire EventType\\\" column, but t